Campus Map       Search                 View Menu  Down arrow icon            Breadcrumbs   College of Nursing    Research    Centers, Labs & Interest Groups        Centers, Labs & Interest Groups  UIC Nursing is home to clusters of researchers working together to pursue solutions to some of the greatest modern health challenges      Groups           Center for Sleep and Health Research  Dedicated to transforming our understanding in order to improve, preserve and promote health through good sleep             Laboratory for Sleep Neurobiology  Focused on basic sleep and brain research, with ongoing studies that examine the consequences of disordered sleep             Midwest Nursing History Research Center  Promoting scholarly research and professional interest in the history of nursing in the Midwest             Exercise/Physical Activity Research Interest Group  Supporting discovery that promotes the health of persons with chronic disease across the lifespan             Diabetes Interest Group              Research    Back to main content           Facilities & Resources    Centers. Labs & Interest Groups     Laboratory for Sleep Neurobiology    Midwest Nursing History Research Center     Midwest Nursing History Research Center Story    Holm Visiting Scholar Award    Collections     Books and journals     Journals    Books after 1960    Books before 1960    Books for young readers    Miscellaneous historical masters theses      Individual nurses    Organizations     Chicago Nurses' Registry Collection    Chicago Public School Nurses' Collection    Emergency Nurses Association Collection    Illinois Association of School Nurses    Illinois Nurses Association    Modeling and Role Modeling    Visiting Nurse Association of Chicago Collection      Schools of nursing     Chicago School of Nursing Collection    Englewood Hospital Training School for Nurses Collection    Illinois Training School for Nurses Collection      Small collections     Nursing Education    Scrapbo